<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 8:29PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...Scattered to numerous showers and thunderstorms producing heavy
rainfall across portions of Portage, Trumbull, northwestern
Mahoning, Geauga, Lake, northeastern Stark, Ashtabula, Erie and
Crawford Counties through 930 PM EDT...
At 826 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated scattered to numerous
showers and thunderstorms across the region, moving northeast at 25
mph. Locally heavy rainfall will continue with ponding of water on
area roadways possible.
HAZARD...Locally heavy rainfall.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Ponding of water on area roadways.
Locations impacted include...
Erie, Youngstown, Warren, Painesville, Ashtabula, Meadville,
Conneaut, Ravenna, Chardon, Fairport Harbor, Geneva-On-The-Lake,
Mentor, Kent, Niles, Tallmadge, North Canton, Streetsboro, Hubbard,
Cortland and Corry.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
